I unfortunately do not get the hype, although I must say I’m glad to see so many people support black business. With that being said we must rise to the occasion and get everything in check. In a time of covid water glasses should not be left upside on the table. A stronger solution needs to be put in the washing machine because glasses have marks and appear embarrassingly dirty. The side plates were dusty and we were given one fork and one knife to tackle multiple different dishes. One being Mac and cheese with no spoon served. The server was good but service was definitely spotty. The drinks were delicious and priced appropriately. The food however was so underwhelming, specifically the soupy Mac and cheese, I needed to triple check to see if they were actually the recipients of best food award by the food network. The price point did not match food but it *is* covid - restaurants are getting by how they see fit.  The pancakes were good, plain. The ambience was fun. They had biggie and an array of 90s throwbacks. If they can get their cleanliness under check and their food back to where it needs to be, I would frequent again.

It also came with a biscuit - try it with the sugar cane butter. We also had the carafe of the Moonshine punch😜...it's good but it sneaks up on you.  They are adhering to social distancing rules by with lower seating capacity, spacing out tables, they have plastic partitions between each table, and temperature checks when you enter the restaurant.  All in all I had a great experience and will definitely be back.

I made reservations in early December for Christmas Eve. I kept checking the website and all of their social media for any indication that there would be a problem. 2 days before Christmas eve they posted a pic of their new outdoor dining which was a sign there would not be a problem with my reservation. THEN they all on CHRISTMAS EVE  3 HOURS BEFORE my reservation to tell me they weren't "technically" open.. I asked why they were just calling me since it was a holiday evening making it hard to make a new reservation and their response was "sorry bout that". NOT  "we'd like to make it up to you" Just "Sorry bout that" Mind you my daughter and I are in town from another state and I had done some specific planning so we could have a great Christmas Eve. Thanks BLVD for nothing...

We wanted so very much to support and love this restaurant. Unfortunately this was not the case on Saturday, December 14. We had 9pm reservations and arrived at approximately 8:30 for drinks. One of the ladies in our party went to bar to order a drink and waited close to 45 minutes for the bartender to take her order. We were seated around 9:30. Our hostess was pleasant, and our server was very friendly and knowledgeable. As we were placing our orders, we learned that the restaurant was out of the following items: Rib eye steak Ribs Pulled pork Watermelon mojito Lobster bisque Southern comfort ice cream Vanilla ice cream Loaded baked potato No desserts except the apple cobbler  The pork chops were extremely salty, as was the potato salad.  However the fried chicken, shrimp & grits and the biscuits were very good. The great music helped to ease the disappointment.  We asked to speak with the manager/owner and communicated our concerns at which time she expressed her complete agreement and dissatisfaction. She heard us without contest, but our overall visit left a stain on our perception of BLVD Bistro.

I think had we been sitting indoors it would have frustrated me but I was in good spirits, the sun was shining and the food was scrumptious.  ****** Update: it’s 2 years later and this place is still to die for. The place is much bigger now, so the it’s lively and more spacious. And the food. Well Still my go to in NYC every tine I visit from London. Go hungry and share everything. (Translated by Google) Small and busy place it is necessary to book at least Sundays for Soul Food brunch.  This type of food is what African-American immigrants brought with them from the southern states.  Basically it is: tasty and hypercaloric. The star dishes are macaroni and cheese (mac'n'cheese) and fried chicken.  However, we did not like the food too much. This is the score of the dishes we tried: Fried chicken - 5/10 Macaroni with 7 cheeses - 7/10 Benedic eggs on crab cake 10/10 Smoked bacon 8/10  The site is very small and they have it bursting with people, it shows in the attitude of the staff that they are overwhelmed, and if they do not wake up they will die of success.  (Original) Lugar pequeño y muy concurrido es necesario reservar al menos los domingos para el brunch al estilo Soul Food.  Este tipo de comida es el que se trajeron consigo los inmigrantes afroamericanos desde los estados del sur.  Básicamente es: sabroso e hipercalórico. Los platos estrella son los macarrones con queso (mac'n'cheese) y el pollo frito.  Sin embargo la comida no nos gustó demasiado. Este es el score de los platos que probamos: Pollo frito - 5 / 10 Macarrones con 7 quesos - 7 / 10 Huevos Benedic sobre pastel de cangrejo 10 /  10 Bacon ahumado 8 / 10  El sitio es muy pequeño y lo tienen a reventar de gente, se nota en la actitud del personal que están sobrepasados, y si no espabilan morirán de éxito.

I have passed this place for many years. Since I go to church up the block from here, and live in the area, I decided to go on an early lunch date, and waited for this establishment to open. Once we walked in, the air was  smoky, and had a heavy aroma of something burnt. We should have left, but decided to stay. The kitchen staff must have burnt something because the smell never left the whole time we were there. They opened up the door to eliminate the smell, but that just made it cold inside. On the menu, they didn't have any of the following available; Shrimp, Catfish, French Toast, or BlueBerry Pancakes. The half and half wasn't very good. The Macaroni and Cheese was burnt on the top. I wonder if that is what the staff was burning in the back. Lobster Bisque is my favorite soup, so since it was the soup of the day, I had to try it. That wasn't bad, came out steaming hot. The chicken, potatoe salad, and collard greens were all very good, but the burnt smell aroma took away from my enjoyment of it. Overall, I was disapointed. I am pretty sure the food is good on any other day, but they  were definitely off their game today.
